org.chemicalmozart.model.implementations.reactionrules

Class MoveToResultRR

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.chemicalmozart.model.implementations.reactionrules.MoveToResultRR
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReactionRule

    public class MoveToResultRR
extends java.lang.Object
implements ReactionRule
    This ReactionRule is used to put a bar into the result solution. It takes the following reagents: (they must appear in this order)
    • SubSolution "barInCreaction"
      • BarInCreation : To identify the bar in creation
      • QuaterLeft : To test in the computeSelect if the bar is full.
    • Subsolution "result"
      • Result : The object that identify the result solution.
    It must put the first subsolution into the second one.

        public java.lang.Object[] computeResult()
        The computeResult must add the BarInCreation solution into the Result solution.
        It must put back the BarInCreation and the QuaterLeft in the BarInCreation solution and then add the BarInCreationSolution into the Result solution. It must also put back the Result object into the Result solution.

      • computeSelect

        public boolean computeSelect()
        The computeSelect has in charge to check that the configuration of the BarInCreation is correct. This means that it must contains a Quaterleft object with a value of 0. It must also contain at least one or several ChordImpl.
        Specified by:

      • getMultiplicity

        public ReactionRule.Multiplicity getMultiplicity()
        Description copied from interface: ReactionRule
        This method must return the multiplicity of the reaction. Two of them exist:

        ONE_SHOT indicates that the reaction will happen only once, the ReactionRule will then be removed from the solution.

        INFINITY_SHOT indicates that the reaction will always happen if reagents are present, until solution inertia. Contrary to OneShot, the ReactionRule will not be removed from the solution after reaction.

        Specified by:
        getMultiplicity in interface ReactionRule
        Returns:
        the multiplicity of the reaction (ONE_SHOT or INFINITY_SHOT).
